00:17:38.460 --> 00:17:41.460
Sam and I are still trying to come up with a school anthem you can groove to.

00:17:56.460 --> 00:17:59.460
Ferguson and Dad's idea of fixing up old chairs

00:17:59.460 --> 00:18:02.460
is turning into a brush with disaster.

00:18:02.460 --> 00:18:15.930
Mom's tearing through the arts and crafts bin for the mother's day in her mind.

00:18:16.930 --> 00:18:20.930
Hey, give the gift that keeps on giving the one you give yourself.

00:18:20.930 --> 00:18:23.930
Do I mind that my mom flipped out?

00:18:23.930 --> 00:18:24.930
Yes.

00:18:24.930 --> 00:18:29.930
Diagnosis, a major bad case of ENS, empty nest syndrome.

00:18:29.930 --> 00:18:31.930
So what's a poor daughter to do?

00:18:31.930 --> 00:18:33.930
Count the days so I leave for good?

00:18:33.930 --> 00:18:35.930
I've got a better idea.

00:18:35.930 --> 00:18:36.930
I've hatched a plan.

00:18:36.930 --> 00:18:39.930
I'm about to make my mom feel so needed in her nest.

00:18:39.930 --> 00:18:41.930
The only thing she'll need will be a break.

00:18:41.930 --> 00:18:50.300
I don't know what it is with my hair,

00:18:50.300 --> 00:18:53.300
but do you think I could give me a hand?

00:18:53.300 --> 00:18:56.300
Oh, well, sure.

00:18:56.300 --> 00:18:58.300
I haven't brushed your hair for you since you were a little girl.

00:18:58.300 --> 00:19:01.300
You were always so much better at it than I was.

00:19:01.300 --> 00:19:04.300
Maybe you could braid it.

00:19:04.300 --> 00:19:07.300
You want me to braid your hair?

00:19:07.300 --> 00:19:08.300
You used to braid it for me.

00:19:08.300 --> 00:19:10.300
Well, not since you were five years old.

00:19:10.300 --> 00:19:12.300
Well, who says those days have to end?

00:19:12.300 --> 00:19:13.300
I miss those days.

00:19:13.300 --> 00:19:15.300
I miss those braids.

00:19:15.300 --> 00:19:18.300
Well, I'm sure you know how to braid your hair yourself.

00:19:18.300 --> 00:19:20.300
Oh, let me get that lemonade.

00:19:20.300 --> 00:19:23.300
Ferguson, we haven't even started working yet.

00:19:23.300 --> 00:19:26.300
Oh, yeah, I know, Dad, but I need to build up my energy.

00:19:26.300 --> 00:19:28.300
I'm still worn out from yesterday.

00:19:28.300 --> 00:19:31.300
Honestly, I did not know this project was going to take this long.

00:19:31.300 --> 00:19:33.300
Yeah, well, maybe if we took fewer breaks, you know...

00:19:33.300 --> 00:19:36.300
Dad, the more we energize, the more productive we'll be

00:19:36.300 --> 00:19:38.300
once we finally get started.

00:19:38.300 --> 00:19:42.300
Hey, Ferguson, maybe mom could help you, you know, be more productive.

00:19:42.300 --> 00:19:44.300
Your mom's busy, Clarissa.

00:19:44.300 --> 00:19:46.300
Yeah, and I'm playing productive when I want to be.

00:19:46.300 --> 00:19:48.300
Oh, really? Well, that's because mom.

00:19:48.300 --> 00:19:51.300
After all, she's the one who taught us how to flap our wings.

00:19:51.300 --> 00:19:55.300
I mean, mom's always got a few good pointers.

00:19:55.300 --> 00:19:57.300
Clarissa, what are you talking about?

00:19:57.300 --> 00:20:01.300
Mom, Ferguson needs you to, um, teach him how to be productive.

00:20:01.300 --> 00:20:03.300
I do not.

00:20:03.300 --> 00:20:04.300
Oh, yes, you do.

00:20:04.300 --> 00:20:07.300
Mom, we love your pep talks.

00:20:07.300 --> 00:20:09.300
Pep talks?

00:20:09.300 --> 00:20:11.300
Yeah, we depend on you to keep us going.

00:20:11.300 --> 00:20:13.300
Right, Ferguson?

00:20:13.300 --> 00:20:15.300
You have something in your eye?

00:20:15.300 --> 00:20:17.300
No.

00:20:17.300 --> 00:20:20.300
I mean, yeah, mom, I need you to help me get something out of my eye.

00:20:20.300 --> 00:20:22.300
What's with her?

00:20:22.300 --> 00:20:25.300
I don't know. Let's go, Ferguson.

00:20:25.300 --> 00:20:27.300
Clarissa, I don't see anything.

00:20:27.300 --> 00:20:30.300
Oh, well, you must have gotten it. It feels so much better.

00:20:30.300 --> 00:20:32.300
Great, but I don't think I did anything.

00:20:32.300 --> 00:20:34.300
Must have been an eyelash.

00:20:34.300 --> 00:20:37.300
You just have that magic mom touch.

00:20:37.300 --> 00:20:40.300
Say, mom, do you think this shirt goes with this

00:20:40.300 --> 00:20:42.300
or should I change it to that green one?

00:20:42.300 --> 00:20:45.300
Since when do you need help picking out your clothes?

00:20:45.300 --> 00:20:48.300
A girl always needs her mom's clothes advice.

00:20:48.300 --> 00:20:51.300
I may not always follow it, but let's just say I'm finally mature enough

00:20:51.300 --> 00:20:53.300
to admit how much I need it.

00:20:53.300 --> 00:20:55.300
Clarissa, if anything, I could go to you for clothes advice.

00:20:55.300 --> 00:20:57.300
You've already left me way behind.

00:20:57.300 --> 00:20:59.300
No, I haven't.

00:20:59.300 --> 00:21:02.470
What do you mean?

00:21:02.470 --> 00:21:04.470
You are the best cook around here.

00:21:04.470 --> 00:21:07.470
I don't know what I'd do if it wasn't for your neck for food.

00:21:07.470 --> 00:21:10.470
Do you think maybe you could pack my lunch for me tomorrow?

00:21:10.470 --> 00:21:13.470
I stopped packing your lunches for you years ago.

00:21:13.470 --> 00:21:15.470
How about once for old times' sake?

00:21:15.470 --> 00:21:17.470
Well, Clarissa, I think it's better if you do it for yourself.

00:21:17.470 --> 00:21:19.470
That way you get the things you like.

00:21:19.470 --> 00:21:21.470
Mom, let's get something straight.

00:21:21.470 --> 00:21:22.470
Uh-huh.

00:21:22.470 --> 00:21:31.100
I need a glass of milk.

00:21:31.100 --> 00:21:33.100
Yeah, a glass of milk.

00:21:33.100 --> 00:21:45.340
So much for plan A.

00:21:45.340 --> 00:21:47.340
I guess she's just so busy showering herself with attention

00:21:47.340 --> 00:21:49.340
that she's not getting from anywhere else

00:21:49.340 --> 00:21:52.340
that she doesn't need any attention from me.

00:21:52.340 --> 00:21:57.150
Hi, Sam.

00:21:57.150 --> 00:22:00.150
Hey, Clarissa. How's this?

00:22:00.150 --> 00:22:04.150
Tommy Stubber High.

00:22:04.150 --> 00:22:07.460
Tommy Stubber High.

00:22:07.460 --> 00:22:10.460
Tommy, Tommy, Tommy, Tommy.

00:22:10.460 --> 00:22:13.460
Tommy Stubber High.

00:22:13.460 --> 00:22:16.460
Definitely Hipper, but can't it stand the test of time?

00:22:16.460 --> 00:22:19.460
Well, honestly, it could be the start of a whole new song cycle.

00:22:19.460 --> 00:22:22.460
Tommy Stubber, the high school wizard.

00:22:22.460 --> 00:22:24.460
He could even go on Broadway.

00:22:24.460 --> 00:22:26.460
Could be a sensation.

00:22:26.460 --> 00:22:27.460
Well, I got an idea.

00:22:27.460 --> 00:22:29.460
Let's go downstairs and ask my mom.

00:22:29.460 --> 00:22:30.460
Your mom?

00:22:30.460 --> 00:22:31.460
Well...

00:22:31.460 --> 00:22:33.460
She's still singing E&S blues?

00:22:33.460 --> 00:22:37.460
Look, Sam, every day is now Mother's Day in the House of Darling.

00:22:37.460 --> 00:22:40.460
I tried to make her feel needed, but I think all I do is confuse her.

00:22:40.460 --> 00:22:42.460
I think you should just talk to her.

00:22:42.460 --> 00:22:44.460
I tried. She's so distracted.

00:22:44.460 --> 00:22:48.460
Well, when I just tell her to save E&S for when the nest is really empty.

00:22:48.460 --> 00:22:50.460
You're right. She's got premature E&S.

00:22:50.460 --> 00:22:52.460
She'll snap out of it.

00:22:52.460 --> 00:22:54.460
Look, I've got to clean up my nest.

00:22:54.460 --> 00:22:56.460
I mean my room. Bye, Clarissa.

00:22:56.460 --> 00:23:00.730
Bye, Sam.

00:23:00.730 --> 00:23:02.730
I guess the nest will really be empty soon enough.

00:23:02.730 --> 00:23:04.730
I'll be going to college.

00:23:04.730 --> 00:23:08.730
I'll be living away from home hundreds, maybe thousands of miles away.

00:23:08.730 --> 00:23:10.730
Never to come home to roost again.

00:23:10.730 --> 00:23:11.730
The rain.

00:23:11.730 --> 00:23:13.730
I'll always remember the rain.

00:23:13.730 --> 00:23:17.730
Standing there, afraid to go, afraid to stay.

00:23:17.730 --> 00:23:22.730
It seemed to wash away all thoughts, all time, all my life.

00:23:22.730 --> 00:23:25.730
And finally, I could see the world clearly.

00:23:25.730 --> 00:23:29.730
Finally, when it would do me no good.

00:23:29.730 --> 00:23:32.730
Clarissa, I made you this pound cake.

00:23:32.730 --> 00:23:39.040
Mother.

00:23:39.040 --> 00:23:40.040
Mother.

00:23:40.040 --> 00:23:41.040
You didn't need to do that.

00:23:41.040 --> 00:23:42.040
I know.

00:23:42.040 --> 00:23:44.040
You don't need me to do anything for you anymore.

00:23:44.040 --> 00:23:46.040
You can do it all for yourself.

00:23:46.040 --> 00:23:48.040
Now that's just foolishness.

00:23:48.040 --> 00:23:49.040
Visit?

00:23:49.040 --> 00:23:52.040
It was only yesterday you were so tiny.

00:23:52.040 --> 00:23:53.040
My little girl.

00:23:53.040 --> 00:23:54.040
And now.

00:23:54.040 --> 00:23:56.040
And now.

00:23:56.040 --> 00:23:58.040
And now you're all grown up.

00:23:58.040 --> 00:24:00.040
You must be strong.

00:24:01.040 --> 00:24:03.040
Let me dry your tears.

00:24:04.040 --> 00:24:07.470
Be your little girl.

00:24:07.470 --> 00:24:09.470
This will always be home.

00:24:09.470 --> 00:24:12.470
And I will always have time for you.

00:24:13.470 --> 00:24:15.470
Mother, I have to go.

00:24:15.470 --> 00:24:17.470
I can't say goodbye.

00:24:17.470 --> 00:24:20.470
And say au revoir.

00:24:25.470 --> 00:24:27.470
Keep in touch, will you?

00:24:27.470 --> 00:24:39.930
You grow up.

00:24:39.930 --> 00:24:41.930
You start doing everything for yourself.

00:24:41.930 --> 00:24:43.930
You leave home to make it on your own.

00:24:43.930 --> 00:24:45.930
Hey, is that any way to treat a mom?

00:24:45.930 --> 00:24:47.930
Why didn't I think of this before?

00:24:47.930 --> 00:24:50.930
If my mom has a premature case of empty nest syndrome,

00:24:50.930 --> 00:24:52.930
I must have a premature case of LNS.

00:24:52.930 --> 00:24:54.930
Leaving nest syndrome.

00:24:54.930 --> 00:24:57.930
Is this a contagious disease or what?

00:24:57.930 --> 00:24:59.930
I better spend some quality time with my mom

00:24:59.930 --> 00:25:01.930
before our time together is over.

00:25:01.930 --> 00:25:04.930
And my premature LNS gets even worse.

00:25:04.930 --> 00:25:11.980
Hi, Clarissa.

00:25:11.980 --> 00:25:14.980
You sure are spending a lot of time up here.

00:25:14.980 --> 00:25:16.980
Oh, it's just something I'm working on.

00:25:16.980 --> 00:25:17.980
I know, Mom.

00:25:17.980 --> 00:25:18.980
I understand.

00:25:18.980 --> 00:25:21.980
Mom, I was just wondering if maybe we could spend

00:25:21.980 --> 00:25:24.980
some more, you know, quality time together.

00:25:24.980 --> 00:25:25.980
Quality time?

00:25:25.980 --> 00:25:27.980
Yeah, you know.

00:25:27.980 --> 00:25:29.980
Girl to girl, woman to woman, mother to daughter,

00:25:29.980 --> 00:25:30.980
that kind of thing.

00:25:30.980 --> 00:25:33.980
Oh, well, um, sure.

00:25:33.980 --> 00:25:40.370
What should we do?

00:25:40.370 --> 00:25:41.370
Maybe we should just talk.

00:25:41.370 --> 00:25:42.370
Great idea.

00:25:42.370 --> 00:25:47.420
So what do you want to talk about?

00:25:47.420 --> 00:25:49.420
I don't know.

00:25:49.420 --> 00:25:53.020
What about Mobius strips?

00:25:53.020 --> 00:25:55.020
Mobius strips? What about them?

00:25:55.020 --> 00:25:57.020
You know what's so cool about them?

00:25:57.020 --> 00:25:59.020
That there's no inside or outside,

00:25:59.020 --> 00:26:00.020
that there's only one side?

00:26:00.020 --> 00:26:01.020
Yeah.

00:26:01.020 --> 00:26:04.020
Do you know that reminds me of my very first boyfriend?

00:26:04.020 --> 00:26:05.020
Timmy Hackensash.

00:26:05.020 --> 00:26:07.020
My sixth grade sweetheart.

00:26:07.020 --> 00:26:09.020
He really was into origami.

00:26:09.020 --> 00:26:11.020
So I folded up this note to him.

00:26:11.020 --> 00:26:14.020
Only by mistake I wrote the note on the back of my homework.

00:26:14.020 --> 00:26:15.020
Do you like it?

00:26:15.020 --> 00:26:16.020
I don't remember.

00:26:16.020 --> 00:26:19.020
But it's the first time I got a bad mark for neatness.

00:26:19.020 --> 00:26:20.020
Can you believe it?

00:26:20.020 --> 00:26:22.020
I just remembered.

00:26:22.020 --> 00:26:24.020
I had a dream last night about math.

00:26:24.020 --> 00:26:27.020
I was a fraction on the run from an eraser.

00:26:27.020 --> 00:26:29.020
Wow, how astride.

00:26:29.020 --> 00:26:31.020
You have the most amazing imagination.

00:26:31.020 --> 00:26:33.020
Actually, we were all fractions.

00:26:33.020 --> 00:26:35.020
You, me, Dad, Bergson.

00:26:35.020 --> 00:26:37.020
I wonder what it means.

00:26:37.020 --> 00:26:40.020
Well, dreams are so strange that...

00:26:40.020 --> 00:26:41.020
I've got it.

00:26:41.020 --> 00:26:42.020
What?

00:26:42.020 --> 00:26:44.020
Well, in my dream we were all different fractions.

00:26:44.020 --> 00:26:46.020
But together we added up to a whole.

00:26:46.020 --> 00:26:47.020
A unit.

00:26:47.020 --> 00:26:48.020
A family.

00:26:48.020 --> 00:26:50.020
What a nice thought.

00:26:50.020 --> 00:26:52.020
Sometimes isn't everything just great.

00:26:52.020 --> 00:26:55.020
Yeah. It's nice to see you feeling so...

00:26:55.020 --> 00:26:56.020
Great?

00:26:56.020 --> 00:26:58.020
Yeah, it's great.

00:26:58.020 --> 00:27:00.020
Now I really better get going.

00:27:00.020 --> 00:27:02.020
Going? Where are you going?

00:27:02.020 --> 00:27:04.020
Oh, I just have to drop something off.

00:27:04.020 --> 00:27:06.020
But we just sat down together.

00:27:06.020 --> 00:27:08.020
Clarissa, I'll be back.

00:27:08.020 --> 00:27:12.020
But you've been so busy and I just wanted to spend some time with you.

00:27:12.020 --> 00:27:14.020
Well, usually you're the one who's so busy.

00:27:14.020 --> 00:27:16.020
